. I’m also wondering if I should consider Checkstyle with a hidden field while handling exceptions properly, ensuring not to mix up `MalformedURLException` with `IOException`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the failing test by making the custom test `ClassLoader` implement both lookup paths used here:\n\n- `ResourceBundle.getBundle(...)` needs `ClassLoader#getResource(...)` to find the `.properties` bundle.\n- `RefCapablePropertyResourceBundle$1.run(...)` then uses `ClassLoader#getResourceAsStream(...)` for the referenced `.text` file.\n\nUpdated:\n- `tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/RefCapablePropertyResourceBundleAnonymous1Test.java`\n\nThe test now serves the in-memory `.properties` resource via a custom in-memory `URL`, and still records `getResourceAsStream(...)` calls for the referenced `.text` resource path. This should resolve the `MissingResourceException` while keeping the active dynamic-access call site exercised.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_001072dd249c3c05016a11962acbf881a083b111738ca14ee8\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1345, "output": 699, "cacheRead": 55808, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57852, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779537438125, "responseId": "resp_001072dd249c3c05016a11961f20f081a09fa4b77759ec6252"}, "toolResults": []}
